      "content": "The line between \"disinformation\" and \"perspective\" is drawn by objective evidence, not subjective feelings, and we must reject the idea that all differing views are equally valid. When a claim is demonstrably false based on verifiable facts, it is disinformation regardless of how many people believe it or how much it aligns with their worldview. We cannot let the subjective nature of political disagreement excuse the deliberate spreading of lies that destroy trust in our institutions.",
